HOW PLAN B for BORIS WORKS (SHARE SHARE SHARE)
The plan is to segregate all vulnerable people (older, ill and at risk) let’s call this group A

Anyone looking after the older,ill and at risk can be group B

The general population generally healthy can be group C

Group C needs to go about it’s business keeping the country moving kids at school us at work

Group B looks after group A and avoids contact with C

Group C is allowed to contract the virus and because it’s generally healthy it can cope with it better than group A

Group A and B are almost self isolating without the virus to avoid putting strain on the NHS and reducing the risk of getting the virus and then needing the NHS

Group C (the generally healthy) go through the cycle of contracting the virus self isolating and being looked after by healthy family members, friends and the local community
Anyone who has complications gets looked after by the NHS while groups A and B are kept away The NHS are not strained by A and B while its looking after complicated cases in C

As group C comes full circle and recovers it divides in to groups that take group B’s position looking after group A allowing group B to go though the cycle

With B and C though the cycle
A is free to have NHS to itself because B and C are now clear from illness and infection and hopefully have a degree of immunity from getting it again this season.

Hope this helps those that are worried or not sure of the plan

snippet.textDisplay:
The coronavirus keeps spreading and a number of prisons in China are now reporting cases of infection. The Chinese Communist Party's (CCP) official media have also admitted that several hundred cases of infection have been confirmed in the prison system.

The outside world nonetheless remains skeptical about the figures revealed by the CCP, believing that the actual number of infections is much higher as it is extremely difficult to contain an infection, especially given the high population density in China's prisons. Many infected prison staff are waiting helplessly for a cure.

Ms. Li, a Falun Gong practitioner in the United States, collected over 200 phone numbers for prison employees in Hubei Province. She has been placing calls to prison staff to talk to them about how they can stay safe in the face of the epidemic. Ms. Li reports that one-third of the people she has called have been infected with the novel coronavirus and have asked for help online.

Ms. Li tells those who answer her calls that tens of thousands of innocent Falun Gong practitioners have been imprisoned and subjected to all kinds of torture for holding fast their faith in Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance. Many practitioners have become disabled, have died from torture, or died after having their organs harvested while they were still alive.

She urges the prison employees to sever ties with the CCP to avoid being held responsible for the crimes the CCP has committed against Falun Gong practitioners. She reminds them that many people have seen their health restored and have averted danger by withdrawing from the CCP and sincerely reciting “Falun Dafa is good, Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance is good.” Many prison employees she's talked to have thanked Ms. Li for thinking of them and telling them how to stay safe amidst the epidemic.

Prison Warden: “I Will Do What You Said Straight Away”
A family member of a prison warden had been infected with the virus and quarantined in their own home as they could not get a bed in a hospital.

When the warden initially received a phone call from Ms. Li, he said dismissively, “You should first check out who I am before starting to tell me the stuff you're propagating.”

“You sound like someone in a senior position,” Ms. Li replied patiently. “Whether you're rich or hold a high-ranking position, you can lose your life very quickly once infected. We only hope that you are all safe.”

The prison warden changed his tone and quietly said, “Thank you.”

“I'm glad you understand what I mean,” said Ms. Li. “You seem to have a good understanding.”

“Oh, thank you,” the prison warden said. “Please tell me what you want to say. I'm listening.”

“The CCP has been persecuting Falun Gong for more than 20 years. I trust that you have seen what Falun Gong practitioners are truly like. We care about people and want to tell you how to stay safe during the outbreak.”
